{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Humans in the developed world"},{"time":2000,"text":"spend more than 90 percent of their lives indoors,"},{"time":5000,"text":"where they breathe in and come into contact"},{"time":8000,"text":"with trillions of life forms invisible to the naked eye:"},{"time":11000,"text":"microorganisms."},{"time":13000,"text":"Buildings are complex ecosystems"},{"time":15000,"text":"that are an important source"},{"time":17000,"text":"of microbes that are good for us,"},{"time":19000,"text":"and some that are bad for us."},{"time":21000,"text":"What determines the types and distributions"},{"time":24000,"text":"of microbes indoors?"},{"time":26000,"text":"Buildings are colonized by airborne microbes"},{"time":29000,"text":"that enter through windows"},{"time":31000,"text":"and through mechanical ventilation systems."},{"time":34000,"text":"And they are brought inside"},{"time":36000,"text":"by humans and other creatures."},{"time":39000,"text":"The fate of microbes indoors"},{"time":41000,"text":"depends on complex interactions"},{"time":43000,"text":"with humans,"},{"time":45000,"text":"and with the human-built environment."},{"time":47000,"text":"And today, architects and biologists"},{"time":49000,"text":"are working together"},{"time":51000,"text":"to explore smart building design"},{"time":54000,"text":"that will create"},{"time":56000,"text":"healthy buildings for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"We spend an extraordinary amount of time"},{"time":61000,"text":"in buildings"},{"time":63000,"text":"that are extremely controlled environments,"},{"time":66000,"text":"like this building here --"},{"time":68000,"text":"environments that have mechanical ventilation systems"},{"time":71000,"text":"that include filtering,"},{"time":73000,"text":"heating and air conditioning."},{"time":75000,"text":"Given the amount of time that we spend indoors,"},{"time":77000,"text":"it's important to understand"},{"time":79000,"text":"how this affects our health."},{"time":81000,"text":"At the Biology and the Built Environment Center,"},{"time":84000,"text":"we carried out a study in a hospital"},{"time":87000,"text":"where we sampled air"},{"time":89000,"text":"and pulled the DNA"},{"time":91000,"text":"out of microbes in the air."},{"time":93000,"text":"And we looked at three different types of rooms."},{"time":96000,"text":"We looked at rooms that were mechanically ventilated,"},{"time":98000,"text":"which are the data points in the blue."},{"time":100000,"text":"We looked at rooms that were naturally ventilated,"},{"time":103000,"text":"where the hospital let us turn off the mechanical ventilation"},{"time":105000,"text":"in a wing of the building"},{"time":107000,"text":"and pry open the windows"},{"time":109000,"text":"that were no longer operable,"},{"time":111000,"text":"but they made them operable for our study."},{"time":113000,"text":"And we also sampled the outdoor air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115000,"text":"If you look at the x-axis of this graph,"},{"time":118000,"text":"you'll see that what we commonly want to do --"},{"time":121000,"text":"which is keeping the outdoors out --"},{"time":123000,"text":"we accomplished that with mechanical ventilation."},{"time":126000,"text":"So if you look at the green data points,"},{"time":128000,"text":"which is air that's outside,"},{"time":130000,"text":"you'll see that there's a large amount of microbial diversity,"},{"time":133000,"text":"or variety of microbial types."},{"time":135000,"text":"But if you look at the blue data points,"},{"time":137000,"text":"which is mechanically ventilated air,"},{"time":139000,"text":"it's not as diverse."},{"time":142000,"text":"But being less diverse"},{"time":144000,"text":"is not necessarily good for our health."},{"time":146000,"text":"If you look at the y-axis of this graph,"},{"time":149000,"text":"you'll see that, in the mechanically ventilated air,"},{"time":152000,"text":"you have a higher probability"},{"time":154000,"text":"of encountering a potential pathogen,"},{"time":156000,"text":"or germ,"},{"time":158000,"text":"than if you're outdoors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160000,"text":"So to understand why this was the case,"},{"time":163000,"text":"we took our data"},{"time":165000,"text":"and put it into an ordination diagram,"},{"time":167000,"text":"which is a statistical map"},{"time":169000,"text":"that tells you something"},{"time":171000,"text":"about how related the microbial communities are"},{"time":173000,"text":"in the different samples."},{"time":175000,"text":"The data points that are closer together"},{"time":177000,"text":"have microbial communities that are more similar"},{"time":180000,"text":"than data points that are far apart."},{"time":182000,"text":"And the first things that you can see from this graph"},{"time":184000,"text":"is, if you look at the blue data points,"},{"time":186000,"text":"which are the mechanically ventilated air,"},{"time":189000,"text":"they're not simply a subset of the green data points,"},{"time":192000,"text":"which are the outdoor air."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194000,"text":"What we've found is that mechanically ventilated air"},{"time":197000,"text":"looks like humans."},{"time":199000,"text":"It has microbes on it"},{"time":201000,"text":"that are commonly associated with our skin"},{"time":204000,"text":"and with our mouth, our spit."},{"time":206000,"text":"And this is because"},{"time":208000,"text":"we're all constantly shedding microbes."},{"time":210000,"text":"So all of you right now"},{"time":212000,"text":"are sharing your microbes with one another."},{"time":214000,"text":"And when you're outdoors,"},{"time":216000,"text":"that type of air has microbes"},{"time":218000,"text":"that are commonly associated with plant leaves and with dirt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"Why does this matter?"},{"time":223000,"text":"It matters because the health care industry"},{"time":225000,"text":"is the second most energy intensive industry"},{"time":228000,"text":"in the United States."},{"time":230000,"text":"Hospitals use two and a half times"},{"time":232000,"text":"the amount of energy as office buildings."},{"time":235000,"text":"And the model that we're working with"},{"time":237000,"text":"in hospitals,"},{"time":239000,"text":"and also with many, many different buildings,"},{"time":241000,"text":"is to keep the outdoors out."},{"time":243000,"text":"And this model"},{"time":245000,"text":"may not necessarily be the best for our health."},{"time":248000,"text":"And given the extraordinary amount"},{"time":250000,"text":"of nosocomial infections,"},{"time":252000,"text":"or hospital-acquired infections,"},{"time":255000,"text":"this is a clue that it's a good time"},{"time":257000,"text":"to reconsider our current practices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"So just as we manage national parks,"},{"time":263000,"text":"where we promote the growth of some species"},{"time":265000,"text":"and we inhibit the growth of others,"},{"time":268000,"text":"we're working towards thinking about buildings"},{"time":271000,"text":"using an ecosystem framework"},{"time":273000,"text":"where we can promote the kinds of microbes"},{"time":276000,"text":"that we want to have indoors."},{"time":280000,"text":"I've heard somebody say"},{"time":282000,"text":"that you're as healthy as your gut."},{"time":284000,"text":"And for this reason, many people eat probiotic yogurt"},{"time":287000,"text":"so they can promote a healthy gut flora."},{"time":290000,"text":"And what we ultimately want to do"},{"time":292000,"text":"is to be able to use this concept"},{"time":295000,"text":"to promote a healthy group"},{"time":297000,"text":"of microorganisms inside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}